<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFF0682D459A3409B866FE5C" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF0682D459A3409B866FE5C" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D459A3409BB39FE91" bold="true" box="[199,322,258,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF0682D44BD3408B8BAFE90" authority="Cartwright &amp; Dostine, 2022" authorityName="Cartwright &amp; Dostine" authorityYear="2022" box="[480,705,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radonica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D44BD3408B8BAFE90" box="[480,705,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Ecnomina radonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D47973408B95DFE90" bold="true" box="[714,806,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2194045FFF0682D47973408B95DFE90" box="[714,806,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF0682D41743408BF33FE90" authority="Neboiss 1979" authorityName="Neboiss" authorityYear="1979" box="[1065,1352,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thinotes">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D41743408BED8FE90" box="[1065,1187,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">E. thinotes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF0682D41F03408BF33FE90" author="Neboiss, A." box="[1197,1352,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" pagination="825 - 843" refId="ref15315" refString="Neboiss, A. (1979 [&quot; 1978 &quot;]) A review of caddis flies from three coastal islands of south-eastern Queensland (Insecta: Trichoptera). Australian Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research, 29 (6), 825 - 843. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / MF 9780825" type="journal article" year="1979">Neboiss 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF0682D40D93408BBC2FECC" authority="Cartwright 1990" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volsellus">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D40D93408BA82FECC" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">E. volsellus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF0682D445D342CBBC2FECC" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[256,441,295,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref14543" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (1990) The Australian species of Ecnomus McLachlan (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Memoirs of the Museum of Victoria, 51, 1 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j / mmv. 1990.51.01" type="journal article" year="1990">
Cartwright 
<quantity id="4CA68CC9FFF0682D44DC342CBBC2FECC" box="[385,441,295,321]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0546" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" unit="in" value="1990.0">1990</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in possessing an elongate pair of simple dorsal processes on tergum X but can be distinguished from the latter two and all other species in the genus by the distinctive, slender and incurved, pincer-like inferior appendages. The wing venation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF0682D47DA3464B976FE04" authority="Cartwright &amp; Dostine, 2022" authorityName="Cartwright &amp; Dostine" authorityYear="2022" box="[647,781,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radonica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D47DA3464B976FE04" box="[647,781,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">E. radonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D464A3464B909FE04" bold="true" box="[791,882,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2194045FFF0682D464A3464B909FE04" box="[791,882,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF0682D46D93464B9BCFE04" box="[900,967,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[285,1294,852,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-131@4.[277,1310,842,1877]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Ecnomina radonica sp. nov. 1, right forewing and apex of hind wing, dorsal. 2–4, male genitalia: 2, left lateral; 3, ventral; 4, dorsal. 5, female genitalia, ventral. Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; dors. pro. terg. X = dorsal process of tergum X (paired); inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559739/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) differs from those figured for 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF0682D40683464BB54FE20" authority="Neboiss 1977" authorityName="Neboiss" authorityYear="1977" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="legula">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D40683464BFE7FE04" box="[1333,1436,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">E. legula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF0682D45CA3498BB54FE20" author="Neboiss, A." box="[151,303,403,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" pagination="1 - 208" refId="ref15259" refString="Neboiss, A. (1977) A taxonomic and zoogeographic study of Tasmanian caddis flies (Insecta: Trichoptera). Memoirs of the National Museum of Victoria, 38, 1 - 208, pls. 201 - 203. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 1977.38.01" type="journal article" year="1977">Neboiss 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF0682D443E3498B8F6FE20" authority="Cartwright 2008" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="2008" box="[355,653,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutica">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D443E3498BBABFE21" box="[355,464,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">E. scutica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF0682D448B3498B8F6FE20" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[470,653,403,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref14639" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2008) A review of the Australian species of Ecnomina Kimmins and Daternomina Neboiss (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Zootaxa, 1774 (1), 1 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1774.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">Cartwright 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF0682D47C63498B92CFE20" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[667,855,403,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref14639" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2008) A review of the Australian species of Ecnomina Kimmins and Daternomina Neboiss (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Zootaxa, 1774 (1), 1 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1774.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">Cartwright 2008</bibRefCitation>
, figs 3, 5), in that forewing forks 2, 3, and 4 and hind wing fork 3 are all relatively short.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFF0682D459A34D1B9CEFC44" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF0682D459A34D1BFF8FD40" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D459A34D1B86EFE79" bold="true" box="[199,533,474,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Description, male &amp; female.</emphasis>
Spurs: 3:4:4. Wings (slightly damaged) as in 
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF0682D414934D0BE2DFE78" box="[1044,1110,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[285,1294,852,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-131@4.[277,1310,842,1877]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Ecnomina radonica sp. nov. 1, right forewing and apex of hind wing, dorsal. 2–4, male genitalia: 2, left lateral; 3, ventral; 4, dorsal. 5, female genitalia, ventral. Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; dors. pro. terg. X = dorsal process of tergum X (paired); inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559739/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. Head, body, and wings light brown; wings similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF0682D475E34F4B81CFD94" authorityName="Neboiss" authorityYear="1977" box="[515,615,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="legula">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D475E34F4B81CFD94" box="[515,615,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">E. legula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF0682D472834F4B94AFD94" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[629,817,511,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref14639" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2008) A review of the Australian species of Ecnomina Kimmins and Daternomina Neboiss (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Zootaxa, 1774 (1), 1 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1774.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">Cartwright 2008</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 3) but most forks shorter. Length of each forewing: male 
<quantity id="4CA68CC9FFF0682D458A3729BB18FDB0" box="[215,355,546,573]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" unit="mm" value="2.45" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.5 mm</quantity>
, female 
<quantity id="4CA68CC9FFF0682D449B3728B859FDB0" box="[454,546,547,573]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
. Forewing with forks 2, 3, 4, and 5 and discoidal cell; fork 2 relatively long, sessile, length of fork about 1.6–1.7 times length of fork 3; fork 3 relatively short, with long footstalk, fork about 1.7–1.8 times length footstalk, crossveins 
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D47293760B8E7FD09" box="[628,668,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">r-m</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D47883760B892FD09" box="[725,745,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">m</emphasis>
nearly contiguous at fork 3, fork 4 about 0.8 times length of fork 3; fork 5 long, length about 1.9–2.0 times length of fork 4. Hind wing with forks 2, 3, and 5 and discoidal cell; fork 2 with short footstalk, length of fork 2 about 2.0–2.3 times length of fork 3; fork 3 shorter than its footstalk.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF0682D45CA37DCB873FC0C" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D45CA37DCBAA3FD7C" box="[151,216,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Male.</emphasis>
Tergum X with one pair of relatively slender dorsal processes (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF0682D46C337DCBE79FD7C" box="[926,1026,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[285,1294,852,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-131@4.[277,1310,842,1877]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Ecnomina radonica sp. nov. 1, right forewing and apex of hind wing, dorsal. 2–4, male genitalia: 2, left lateral; 3, ventral; 4, dorsal. 5, female genitalia, ventral. Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; dors. pro. terg. X = dorsal process of tergum X (paired); inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559739/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Figs 2, 4</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view robust in basal third (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF0682D45FD37F0BA9CFC98" box="[160,231,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[285,1294,852,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-131@4.[277,1310,842,1877]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Ecnomina radonica sp. nov. 1, right forewing and apex of hind wing, dorsal. 2–4, male genitalia: 2, left lateral; 3, ventral; 4, dorsal. 5, female genitalia, ventral. Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; dors. pro. terg. X = dorsal process of tergum X (paired); inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559739/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Superior appendages slender, somewhat rod-like (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF0682D466B37F0B9E5FC98" box="[822,926,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[285,1294,852,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-131@4.[277,1310,842,1877]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Ecnomina radonica sp. nov. 1, right forewing and apex of hind wing, dorsal. 2–4, male genitalia: 2, left lateral; 3, ventral; 4, dorsal. 5, female genitalia, ventral. Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; dors. pro. terg. X = dorsal process of tergum X (paired); inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559739/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Figs 2, 4</figureCitation>
), in lateral view with length about 6.8 times width (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF0682D45BA3614BB57FCB4" box="[231,300,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[285,1294,852,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-131@4.[277,1310,842,1877]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Ecnomina radonica sp. nov. 1, right forewing and apex of hind wing, dorsal. 2–4, male genitalia: 2, left lateral; 3, ventral; 4, dorsal. 5, female genitalia, ventral. Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; dors. pro. terg. X = dorsal process of tergum X (paired); inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559739/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view with length about 5.5 times width, each with single, robust subapical spine (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF0682D40143614BFF4FCB4" box="[1353,1423,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[285,1294,852,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-131@4.[277,1310,842,1877]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Ecnomina radonica sp. nov. 1, right forewing and apex of hind wing, dorsal. 2–4, male genitalia: 2, left lateral; 3, ventral; 4, dorsal. 5, female genitalia, ventral. Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; dors. pro. terg. X = dorsal process of tergum X (paired); inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559739/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Phallus simple, tube-like (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF0682D44993648B834FCD0" box="[452,591,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[285,1294,852,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-131@4.[277,1310,842,1877]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Ecnomina radonica sp. nov. 1, right forewing and apex of hind wing, dorsal. 2–4, male genitalia: 2, left lateral; 3, ventral; 4, dorsal. 5, female genitalia, ventral. Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; dors. pro. terg. X = dorsal process of tergum X (paired); inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559739/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Figs 2, 3, 4</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages slender, curved strongly downward and mesad like pincers, fused at base (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF0682D44C8366CBB81FC0C" box="[405,506,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[285,1294,852,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-131@4.[277,1310,842,1877]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Ecnomina radonica sp. nov. 1, right forewing and apex of hind wing, dorsal. 2–4, male genitalia: 2, left lateral; 3, ventral; 4, dorsal. 5, female genitalia, ventral. Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; dors. pro. terg. X = dorsal process of tergum X (paired); inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559739/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Figs 2, 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF0682D459A3680B9CEFC44" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D459A3680BB58FC28" box="[199,291,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Female.</emphasis>
Genitalia with a single slender, elongate mesal process on sternite VIII; segment IX relatively long and slender, segment X relatively short and slender in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF0682D463E36A4B9DCFC44" box="[867,935,942,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[285,1294,852,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-131@4.[277,1310,842,1877]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Ecnomina radonica sp. nov. 1, right forewing and apex of hind wing, dorsal. 2–4, male genitalia: 2, left lateral; 3, ventral; 4, dorsal. 5, female genitalia, ventral. Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; dors. pro. terg. X = dorsal process of tergum X (paired); inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559739/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFF0682D459A36D8B9EEFC63" box="[199,917,979,1006]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF0682D459A36D8B9EEFC63" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1077]" box="[199,917,979,1006]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D459A36D8BB35FC60" bold="true" box="[199,334,979,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Etymology.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D440836D8BBBBFC60" box="[341,448,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Radonica</emphasis>
—from the 
<typeStatus id="54E59F8EFFF0682D471E36D8B808FC60" box="[579,627,979,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">type</typeStatus>
locality (Radon Springs).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFF0682D459A36FCBB83FBB8" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF0682D459A36FCBB83FBB8" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D459A36FCBB40FB9C" bold="true" box="[199,315,1015,1041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Remarks.</emphasis>
Ten male specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF0682D471836FCB959FB9C" authorityName="Cartwright &amp; Dostine" authorityYear="2022" box="[581,802,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radonica">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF0682D471836FCB959FB9C" box="[581,802,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">Ecnomina radonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are recorded from three localities within Kakadu NP, NT (latitude range 12.75– 
<geoCoordinate id="EE6A47EBFFF0682D44CE3111BB97FBB8" box="[403,492,1050,1077]" degrees="12.83" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" precision="555" value="-12.83">12.83°S</geoCoordinate>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
